              <h3><strong><font color="#000000" size="3" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Improve the productivity,   morale and motivation of your team.</font></strong></h3>
              <p align="justify"><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Studies show   that a high percentage of employees are in the dark about how well they&rsquo;re doing   on the job or how they can do better. This can result in exceptional employees   being unaware of their strengths. Or, those who feel their efforts are unnoticed   and unappreciated may become demotivated or worse, start looking for another   job. On the flip side, marginal employees may become complacent and assume that   silence on your part means approval. Bottom line: You can't afford to have   employees that leave or drop the ball in today's tight-budgeted, productivity   driven healthcare industry.</font></p>
              <p align="justify"><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Learn   the necessary steps to close this communication gap by registering for this   1-hour audio conference conducted by <strong>Bob Levoy</strong>, who Health   Executive magazine describes as a &ldquo;healthcare management guru.&rdquo; You'll walk away   with practical tools to improve the productivity, morale and motivation of your   team.</font></p>
              <p align="justify"><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>Heres   a sampling of the details youll learn:<br />
              </strong></font></p>
              <ul>
                <li><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">A   step-by-step plan to <strong>make performance reviews more   meanin</strong>gful. </font></li>
                <li><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The   critical document <strong>you need to get started.</strong> </font></li>
                <li><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>Choose   your battles wisely</strong>: what to focus on -- and what to ignore. </font></li>
                <li><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">How   to facilitate a discussion the right way. Hint: <strong>The key is in your   questions.</strong> </font></li>
                <li><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>Make   sure your review produces results</strong>: The secrets of effective feedback. </font></li>
                <li><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The   saddest mistake of performance management -- and <strong>other hard-learned   lessons.</strong></font></li>
                </ul>
              <p><font size="2" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>Who   should attend</strong>?Healthcare providers, nurse managers, practice   administrators, office managers and those with supervisory   responsibilities.</font></p>
